  "title": "Blood values",
  "body_html": "<div>The RCEM expects the following from candidates:<br /><i>'Knowledge of normal adult values for Hb, haematocrit, platelet and white cell counts'</i><br /><br />The following is taken from the RCEM glossary of terms 2022:<br /><br /><div class=\"table-responsive\"><table class = \"tlarge table table-striped table-bordered\"  data-role=\"table\" id=\"tableid1\" ><thead><tr><th>Test</th><th>Normal range</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Haemoglobin</td><td>11.5 - 16.6g/dl</td></tr><tr><td>White blood cells</td><td>4 - 11 x 10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr><td>Platelets</td><td>150 - 450 x 10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr><td>MCV</td><td>80 - 96 fl</td></tr><tr><td>MCHC</td><td>32 - 36 g/dl</td></tr><tr><td>Neutrophils</td><td>2 - 7.5 x 10<sup>9</sup><br />/L</td></tr><tr><td>Lymphocytes</td><td>1.5 - 4 x 10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr><td>Monocytes</td><td>0.3 - 1 x 10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr><td>Eosinophils</td><td>0.1- 0.5 x 10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr><td>Basophils</td><td><0.2 x 10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr><td>Reticulocytes</td><td><2 %</td></tr><tr><td>Haematocrit</td><td>0.35 - 0.49</td></tr><tr><td>Red Cell distribution width</td><td>11 - 15%</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"><table style='width:100%'><tr><td>RCEM</td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_like_469\" data-linkid=\"469\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_good_count_469\" class = \"link_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">0</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_dislike_469\" data-linkid=\"469\" data-rating=\"0\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-down\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-down\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_bad_count_469\" class = \"link_bad_count\" style=\"color:red; font-size:85%;\">0</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://rcem.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Glossary_of_Terms_Used_in_RCEM_Examinations_October_2022.pdf\">Normal values</a></td></tr></table></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodymedia\"></div>\n\n\n<div id=\"categorynum\">2</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategorynum\">1</div>\n\n<div id=\"categoryname\">Physiology</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategoryname\">Cellular & molecular physiology</div>\n<div id=\"mybody\">\n\n<div id=\"body_content\">\nThe RCEM expects the following from candidates:<br /><i>'Knowledge of normal adult values for Hb, haematocrit, platelet and white cell counts'</i><br /><br />The following is taken from the RCEM glossary of terms 2022:<br /><br /><div class=\"table-responsive\"><table class = \"tlarge table table-striped table-bordered\"  data-role=\"table\" id=\"tableid1\" ><thead><tr><th>Test</th><th>Normal range</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Haemoglobin</td><td>11.5 - 16.6g/dl</td></tr><tr><td>White blood cells</td><td>4 - 11 x 10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr><td>Platelets</td><td>150 - 450 x 10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr><td>MCV</td><td>80 - 96 fl</td></tr><tr><td>MCHC</td><td>32 - 36 g/dl</td></tr><tr><td>Neutrophils</td><td>2 - 7.5 x 10<sup>9</sup><br />/L</td></tr><tr><td>Lymphocytes</td><td>1.5 - 4 x 10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr><td>Monocytes</td><td>0.3 - 1 x 10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr><td>Eosinophils</td><td>0.1- 0.5 x 10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr><td>Basophils</td><td><0.2 x 10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr><td>Reticulocytes</td><td><2 %</td></tr><tr><td>Haematocrit</td><td>0.35 - 0.49</td></tr><tr><td>Red Cell distribution width</td><td>11 - 15%</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>\n\n\n<BR><BR><table style='width:100%'><tr><td>RCEM</td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_like_469\" data-linkid=\"469\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\"